dcterms:description: The Spurious-Motif dataset consists of 18000 synthetic graphs. Each graph is generated by attaching one base (Tree, Ladder, Wheel) to a motif (Cycle, House, Crane). The graph label is consistent with the class of motif, and the dataset is used to study the effects of spurious correlations.
dcterms:title: Spurious-Motif

dcterms:description: MUTAG is a dataset of chemical compounds represented as graphs, where the task is to classify the mutagenicity of these compounds. The dataset is commonly used for benchmarking graph neural networks.
dcterms:title: MUTAG

dcterms:creator: M. Knyazev

dcterms:description: The D&D dataset consists of graphs representing protein structures, where the task is to classify the proteins based on their structures. It is widely used for evaluating graph neural networks.
dcterms:title: D&D

dcterms:description: Twitch-Explicit is a dataset containing social networks from the Twitch platform, used for tasks such as node classification and link prediction. It includes multiple social networks related to different locations.
